## Avoid

Never use these in style prompts:

### Genres
- happy electro / euphoric trance / festival EDM
- pop punk / pop rock / radio rock (generic)
- country, bluegrass, americana (unless specifically called for in a project)
- gospel, worship (unless documentary use)
- reggae, ska
- synthwave / outrun / retro-futurism — banned per {{ARTIST_NAME}} aesthetic (no 1980s/90s nostalgia in any layer)

### Descriptors
- happy, upbeat, cheerful, joyful, sunny, bright
- anthemic (unless specifically called for)
- "feel-good", "uplifting", "vibey"
- "summer", "tropical", "party"
- "epic" (overused — describe what you mean specifically)
- "viral", "TikTok-ready"

### Production Terms
- heavy autotune (unless project-justified)
- sidechain pump (unless EDM)
- maximalist
- over-mastered, brick-walled, loudness-war

### Artist Names
- Per `/reference/suno/artist-blocklist.md` — never reference real artists by name; describe the sound instead. Use era descriptions ("late-70s post-punk") not artist names.
- This same ban extends to the system's own functions: never name an alter or function in a metatag. Describe the voice's timbre and register only.

